    "body": "Not sure if this helps but I ran into the same issue and made ColumnPanel\n\nhttps://github.com/dalejung/trtools/blob/master/trtools/core/column_panel.py\n\nI tend to access panel columns and modify a Panel like a DataFrame. It allows you to do things like this:\n\n``` python\npanel = pd.Panel({'aapl':aapl, 'goog':goog})\npanel = trt.ColumnPanel(panel)\n\npanel['returns'] = panel.Close / panel.Close.shift(1) - 1\npanel.returns\n\n<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\nDatetimeIndex: 252 entries, 2011-08-04 00:00:00 to 2012-08-02 00:00:00\nData columns:\naapl    251  non-null values\ngoog    251  non-null values\ndtypes: float64(2)\n\n# item access\npanel.im.aapl\n\n<class 'pandas.core.frame.DataFrame'>\nDatetimeIndex: 252 entries, 2011-08-04 00:00:00 to 2012-08-02 00:00:00\nData columns:\nOpen         252  non-null values\nHigh         252  non-null values\nLow          252  non-null values\nClose        252  non-null values\nVolume       252  non-null values\nAdj Close    252  non-null values\nreturns      251  non-null values\ndtypes: float64(7)\n```\n"
  },
